    <name>Pro Tips: It All Starts With a Goal</name>
    <intro>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{707e2c0e-eebd-4c90-af1e-5c4111040a81}{182}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:10,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.13999,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Pro%20Tip.png" alt="" width="140" height="136" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use case studies in your instruction.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;To introduce an instructional topic, adults will be&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;more&amp;nbsp;engaged by relevant situations (cases) they can&amp;nbsp;relate to, analyze (study) and then apply. As&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;real-life examples, case&amp;nbsp;studies increase relevance, value, and authenticity in learning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/relevance-value-authenticity" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 7.2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Make sure adult learners understand the "why" of goal setting.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;For all learners but especially&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;those with learning differences strategic planning is often a step that is omitted. Help learners&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;strategically plan their goals by sharing them out loud with their peers and providing strategies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;they can use to set goals - such as templates or sample goals(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Action &amp;amp; Expression&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression/executive-functions/strategy-development/strategy-development" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 6.2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Celebrate the accomplishment of small goals.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;When goals are too distant&amp;nbsp;(e.g., “do your&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;best”&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;“make&amp;nbsp;progress”), or&amp;nbsp;when goals seem too easy&amp;nbsp;(or too&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;difficult),&amp;nbsp;progress,&amp;nbsp;performance,&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;motivation are more difficult for learners to reach.&amp;nbsp;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Action&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;amp; Expression&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression/executive-functions/goal-setting/goal-setting" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 6.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use goal-development templates.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Learners who are new at setting goals will benefit from using&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;templates. Setting goals can feel&amp;nbsp;overwhelming at first. The use of a template can simplify the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;process and provide a structure for goal&amp;nbsp;setting&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Action &amp;amp; Expression&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression/executive-functions/goal-setting/goal-setting" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 6.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remember the 10x10x10 Rule.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.gartner.com/smarterwithgartner/4-actions-to-be-a-good-leader-during-covid-19-disruption#:~:text=%E2%80%9C%20The%2010x10x10%20rule%20applies%20here,what%20to%20do%20and%20when." target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@1D59B5,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;People need to hear something 10 times in 10 different&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@1D59B5,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;ways&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;and they will remember 10% of it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Goals are not like a crock-pot. You don’t set them and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;forget&amp;nbsp;them. Once a goal is clearly established with a plan to progress&amp;nbsp;towards&amp;nbsp;it, educators will&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;need to&amp;nbsp;continually bring the goal and plan back into focus. By repeating the objective and plan&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;to achieve it you&amp;nbsp;can help keep learners on track. This reinforcement can take the form of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;assessments, prompts&amp;nbsp;(i.e., my goal is...I’ve gotten closer to this goal by...”, checklists, think—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;aloud, or a weekly check-in.&amp;nbsp;Whether it is a classroom goal or a learner’s personal goal,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;continually refocusing on the&amp;nbsp;objective and steps to get there is critical to maintaining progress&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/effort-persistence/mastery-oriented-feedback" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 8.4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Provide choice and flexibility in how students show they have achieved the learning goal.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Try to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;move away from traditional paper and pencil tasks.&amp;nbsp;Consider performance measures where&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;students demonstrate skill and understanding. Also, consider&amp;nbsp;alternative tasks&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;writing such&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;as&amp;nbsp;drawings, slide presentation, video, or&amp;nbsp;conversation (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/self-regulation/self-assessment-reflection" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 9.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,9," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use formative assessments&amp;nbsp;frequently.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Formative assessments, administered during the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;instructional process, focused on and&amp;nbsp;aligned&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;the sub-steps within the goal, help teachers and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;students monitor and&amp;nbsp;evaluate&amp;nbsp;progress toward&amp;nbsp;the bigger goal. Additionally, information about&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;student&amp;nbsp;understanding during the instructional&amp;nbsp;process helps teachers identify a need for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;course&amp;nbsp;correction if students are not able to&amp;nbsp;clearly&amp;nbsp;demonstrate understanding (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/representation" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Representation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/representation/language-symbols/illustrate-multimedia" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 2.5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Share goal monitoring apps.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Help adult learners use goals for efficiently and effectively by&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;keeping them close at hand on apps. AE learners&amp;nbsp;have busy lives and are often juggling multiple&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;demands. By using apps to set a goal they can&amp;nbsp;have frequent easy access through their&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;digital&amp;nbsp;device. Samples&amp;nbsp;include budgeting apps, nutrition&amp;nbsp;apps, screen time monitoring apps etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Action &amp;amp; Expression&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression/executive-functions/goal-setting/goal-setting" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 6.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;​​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;ol role="list" start="6"&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;ol role="list" start="6"&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;ol role="list" start="6"&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider%20wave.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
